#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.100"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.100:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga "
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.100:0.3"
msgid "100. Loṇakapallasutta "
msgstr "100. A Lump of Salt "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: Yo → yo kho (s1-3, km) | yo ca kho (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:1.1"
msgid "“Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose you say: "

msgctxt "an3.100:1.2"
msgid "‘yathā yathāyaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathā taṃ paṭisaṃvediyatī’ti, evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso na hoti, okāso na paññāyati sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāya. "
msgstr "‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience it the same way.’ This being so, the spiritual life could not be lived, and there’d be no chance of making a complete end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:1.3"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose you say: "

msgctxt "an3.100:1.4"
msgid "‘yathā yathā vedanīyaṃ ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathāssa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvediyatī’ti, evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso hoti, okāso paññāyati sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāya. "
msgstr "‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience the result as it should be experienced.’ This being so, the spiritual life can be lived, and there is a chance of making a complete end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pāpakammaṃ → pāpaṃ kammaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr "Take the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell. "

msgctxt "an3.100:1.6"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr "Meanwhile, another person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.100:2.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti? "
msgstr "What kind of person does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell? "

# NOTE: Bhavitakaya is explained in MN 36 as ability to endure pain, and also in the same sense at Pe 2. See BB’s note for emendation to dukkhavihari.
msgctxt "an3.100:2.2"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhāvitakāyo hoti abhāvitasīlo abhāvitacitto abhāvitapañño paritto appātumo appadukkhavihārī. "
msgstr "A person who hasn’t developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, or wisdom. They’re small-minded and mean-spirited, living in suffering. "

msgctxt "an3.100:2.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr "That kind of person does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.100:3.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva? "
msgstr "What kind of person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot? "

#. VAR: mahatto → mahattā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī. "
msgstr "A person who has developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom. They’re not small-minded, but are big-hearted, living without limits. "

msgctxt "an3.100:3.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr "That kind of person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.250, sc4
#. VAR: loṇakapallaṃ → loṇaphalaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: udakamallake → udakakapallake (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso loṇakapallaṃ paritte udakamallake pakkhipeyya. "
msgstr "Suppose a person was to drop a lump of salt into a small bowl of water. "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

#. VAR: taṃ parittaṃ udakaṃ → udakamallake udakaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.3"
msgid "api nu taṃ parittaṃ udakaṃ amunā loṇakapallena loṇaṃ assa apeyyan”ti? "
msgstr "Would that small bowl of water become salty and undrinkable?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir. "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.5"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.6"
msgid "“Aduñhi, bhante, parittaṃ udakakapallake udakaṃ, taṃ amunā loṇakapallena loṇaṃ assa apeyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Because there is only a little water in the bowl.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:4.7"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso loṇakapallakaṃ gaṅgāya nadiyā pakkhipeyya. "
msgstr "“Suppose a person was to drop a lump of salt into the Ganges river. "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.8"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.9"
msgid "api nu sā gaṅgā nadī amunā loṇakapallena loṇaṃ assa apeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would the Ganges river become salty and undrinkable?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:4.10"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir. "

msgctxt "an3.100:4.11"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

#. VAR: loṇakapallena loṇo na assa apeyyo”ti → loṇaṃ nevassa appeyyoti (bj) | loṇaphalena loṇo assa apeyyoti (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.100:4.12"
msgid "“Asu hi, bhante, gaṅgāya nadiyā mahā udakakkhandho so amunā loṇakapallena loṇo na assa apeyyo”ti. "
msgstr "Because the Ganges river is a vast mass of water.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.100:5.1"
msgid "“Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr "“This is how it is in the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell. "

msgctxt "an3.100:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr "Meanwhile, another person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.100:6.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhāvitakāyo hoti abhāvitasīlo abhāvitacitto abhāvitapañño paritto appātumo appadukkhavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:6.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.100:7.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:7.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:7.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. (1) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.251, sc8
msgctxt "an3.100:8.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "Take the case of a person who is thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars. "

msgctxt "an3.100:8.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "While another person isn’t thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.100:9.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpo, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati? "
msgstr "What kind of person is thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars? "

msgctxt "an3.100:9.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco daliddo hoti appassako appabhogo. "
msgstr "A person who is poor, with few possessions and little wealth. "

msgctxt "an3.100:9.3"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi bandhanaṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "That kind of person is thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.100:10.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpo, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati? "
msgstr "What kind of person isn’t thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars? "

msgctxt "an3.100:10.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo. "
msgstr "A person who is rich, affluent, and wealthy. "

# NOTE: This sutta has a breathtakingly cynical view of the justice system…
msgctxt "an3.100:10.3"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, aḍḍhakahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati, kahāpaṇasatenapi na bandhanaṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "That kind of person isn’t thrown in jail for stealing half a dollar, a dollar, or a hundred dollars. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:10.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ. "
msgstr "This is how it is in the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but they go to hell. "

msgctxt "an3.100:10.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:10.6"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr "Meanwhile, another person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an3.100:11.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:11.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhāvitakāyo hoti abhāvitasīlo abhāvitacitto abhāvitapañño paritto appātumo appadukkhavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:11.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.100:12.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:12.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:12.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. (2) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.252, sc13
msgctxt "an3.100:13.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:13.2"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:13.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā appekaccaṃ urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ, appekaccaṃ urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ. "
msgstr "It’s like a sheep dealer or butcher. They can execute, jail, fine, or otherwise punish one person who steals from them, but not another. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#. VAR: Kathaṃrūpaṃ → kathaṃrūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:14.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ? "
msgstr "What kind of person can they punish? "

msgctxt "an3.100:14.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco daliddo hoti appassako appabhogo. "
msgstr "A person who is poor, with few possessions and little wealth. "

#. VAR: Evarūpaṃ → evarūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:14.3"
msgid "Evarūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ pahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ. "
msgstr "That’s the kind of person they can punish. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
#. VAR: Kathaṃrūpaṃ → kathaṃrūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ. "
msgstr "What kind of person can’t they punish? "

msgctxt "an3.100:15.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco aḍḍho hoti mahaddhano mahābhogo rājā vā rājamahāmatto vā. "
msgstr "A person who is rich, affluent, and wealthy. "

#. VAR: Evarūpaṃ → evarūpo (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.3"
msgid "Evarūpaṃ, bhikkhave, orabbhiko vā urabbhaghātako vā urabbhaṃ adinnaṃ ādiyamānaṃ nappahoti hantuṃ vā bandhituṃ vā jāpetuṃ vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kātuṃ. "
msgstr "That’s the kind of person they can’t punish. "

#. VAR: pañjalikova → pañjaliko (mr)
#. VAR: naṃ → paraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.100:15.4"
msgid "Aññadatthu pañjalikova naṃ yācati: "
msgstr "In fact, all they can do is raise their joined palms and ask: "

msgctxt "an3.100:15.5"
msgid "‘dehi me, mārisa, urabbhaṃ vā urabbhadhanaṃ vā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Please, good sir, give me my sheep or pay me for it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:15.6"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr "This is how it is in the case of a person who does a trivial bad deed, but it lands them in hell. "

msgctxt "an3.100:15.7"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. "
msgstr "Meanwhile, another person does the same trivial bad deed, but experiences it in the present life, without even a bit left over, not to speak of a lot. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.253, sc16
msgctxt "an3.100:16.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:16.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo abhāvitakāyo hoti abhāvitasīlo abhāvitacitto abhāvitapañño paritto appātumo appadukkhavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:16.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa appamattakampi pāpakammaṃ kataṃ tamenaṃ nirayaṃ upaneti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an3.100:17.1"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:17.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo bhāvitakāyo hoti bhāvitasīlo bhāvitacitto bhāvitapañño aparitto mahatto appamāṇavihārī. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.100:17.3"
msgid "Evarūpassa, bhikkhave, puggalassa tādisaṃyeva appamattakaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ diṭṭhadhammavedanīyaṃ hoti, nāṇupi khāyati, kiṃ bahudeva. (3) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an3.100:18.1"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Mendicants, suppose you say: "

msgctxt "an3.100:18.2"
msgid "‘yathā yathāyaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathā taṃ paṭisaṃvedetī’ti, evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso na hoti, okāso na paññāyati sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāya. "
msgstr "‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience it the same way.’ This being so, the spiritual life could not be lived, and there’d be no chance of making a complete end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.100:18.3"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose you say: "

msgctxt "an3.100:18.4"
msgid "‘yathā yathā vedanīyaṃ ayaṃ puriso kammaṃ karoti tathā tathā tassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedetī’ti, evaṃ santaṃ, bhikkhave, brahmacariyavāso hoti, okāso paññāyati sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāyā”ti. "
msgstr "‘No matter how this person performs a deed, they experience the result as it should be experienced.’ This being so, the spiritual life can be lived, and there is a chance of making a complete end of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.100:18.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

